SERVER_PORT=HTTP port the Spring Boot app listens on
SPRING_LOG_LEVEL=Log level for Spring framework packages (e.g. INFO, DEBUG)
LOG_LEVEL=Log level for application packages (e.g. INFO, DEBUG)

VB_URL=Momentum API v2 base URL for the Vidingehem market objects endpoint
VB_API_KEY=API key sent as the auth header to the Momentum API
SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL=Slack incoming webhook URL for notifications
VX_PREFIX_LINK=URL prefix prepended to property IDs when linking from Slack messages

LIST_API_CACHE_DURATION_HOURS=Hours between full list-API syncs
DETAIL_REFRESH_INTERVAL_HOURS=Hours before a house's details are considered stale and refetched
DETAIL_FETCH_MIN_DELAY_SECONDS=Lower bound on the adaptive delay between detail fetches
DETAIL_FETCH_MAX_DELAY_SECONDS=Upper bound on the adaptive delay between detail fetches
DETAIL_FETCH_IDLE_DELAY_SECONDS=Delay used when no houses are active

GEOCODING_ENABLED=Toggles the address-to-coordinates lookup used to populate house.latitude/longitude. Defaults to true; set to false only to stop the sync from calling the geocoder (useful for offline dev or when debugging the provider).
GEOCODING_BASE_URL=Base URL of the geocoding HTTP API. Defaults to https://nominatim.openstreetmap.org (OpenStreetMap Nominatim, free, no API key needed). Only override to point at a self-hosted Nominatim mirror or a drop-in compatible alternative.
GEOCODING_USER_AGENT=User-Agent header sent on every geocoding request. Defaults to "boplats-tracker/1.0". Nominatim's usage policy requires a meaningful, identifiable value (ideally including a contact email), so override this in production deployments — e.g. "boplats-tracker (contact: ops@example.com)".
GEOCODING_RATE_LIMIT_MS=Minimum milliseconds between consecutive geocoding calls. Defaults to 1100 (~1 req/s, the cap Nominatim's usage policy enforces). Only raise this if a provider asks for stricter throttling; do not lower it for the public Nominatim endpoint.

HOSTNAME=Database host as reachable from the app container
DATABASE_PORT=Database TCP port
DATABASE_NAME=Database/schema name
DATABASE_USERNAME=Database user
DATABASE_PASSWORD=Database password
DATABASE_DIALECT=Hibernate dialect class for the target database

HIBERNATE_DDL_AUTO=Hibernate schema-management mode (none, update, validate, etc.)
